[{"id":"VR625280","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div><div class=\"stimulus_reference\"><div class=\"passage\"><div class=\"prose style:1\"><div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure shows a block of mass m attached to the right end of a compressed spring, labeled k, on a horizontal x axis. There are three equally spaced positions, labeled x equals negative A, x equals 0, and x equals A from left to right, on the axis. The block is currently held at the position x equals negative A.\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/578/VR625280.g03.svg\"/></div></div></div></div></div><p class=\"stem_paragraph\">A block is attached to a compressed, horizontal spring. A person is initially holding the block in place at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals negative A\"><math alttext=\"x equals negative A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> as shown in the figure. The person then slowly moves the block at a constant speed through position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals 0\"><math alttext=\"x equals 0\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math></span></span>, at which point the spring is at its relaxed length, and then to position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals positive A\"><math alttext=\"x equals positive A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>. Which of the following correctly describes how the potential energy in the spring-block system changes as the block is moved from <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals negative A\"><math alttext=\"x equals negative A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>−</mo><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span> to <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"x equals positive A\"><math alttext=\"x equals positive A\" display=\"inline\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>+</mo><mtext>A</mtext></math></span></span>?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR625280_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential energy decreases throughout the motion</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential energy increases throughout the motion</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential energy decreases and then increases</p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\">The potential energy increases and then decreases</p>"],"answer":2}]